East Coast Fish & Chips-Simple Stovetop

Ingredients Fish & Chips
-8 pieces of cod fish cleaned and dried, seasoned with salt and pepper
-8-10 potatoes, peeled and sliced into fries, seasoned with salt and pepper 
-4 cups flour + 2 cups breadcrumbs
-2 eggs
-1 bottle of beer
-plenty of canola oil for frying 
-1-2 lemons for garnish 

1.whisk eggs and beer together. Dip cod pieces 2-3 times in beer/egg mix, then do the same but with breadcrumbs

2. Heat oil into two pans. Make sure there’s enough oil to completely cover the fries in one and the fish in the other.

3. Fry potatoes in medium heat into pan in batches without overcrowding the pan. When each batch is done. At the end, put them all back Into the oil and mix around to ensure they are piping hot when serving once fish is ready

4. Fry fish 5 minutes per side. Don’t overcrowd the pan. Give each fillet plenty of space. When cooked, Soak on paper towel to absorb oil.

Tartar sauce:
-1 cup mayo, 1/4 cup diced pickle, 1/4 diced sweet onion, juice of 1 lemon, 1 tbsp of mustard, 1 tbsp chopped fresh or dried dill. Mix altogether in a bowl.

5. Serve with fries, piece of fish, lemon wedge and side of Tartar sauce for dipping

Lately I’ve been thinking about how bizarre it is that we all went through something so traumatic, and nobody came out of it unscathed. So many people lost so much and I believe there is so much undiagnosed PTSD from the pandemic.

So now it’s like it all vanished so suddenly and many of us are left to just figure it out and pick up the pieces of shattered lives and dreams. 

For many of us, our lights are out and spirit is fatigued and there is no support for that. 

When you’re spiritually exhausted, your body will feel fine but you’ll be exhausted, make no mistake: you’re on the right path. 

So, you can’t just go back into the matrix and start living mindlessly again.
Exhaustion means you’ve taken on more information and shifts in perception than your mind can handle. The fact that you were even willing to do this means that you have an open mind, a trait that most people don’t. 

I am only just picking up the pieces and reconnecting with myself because for the last few years I felt lost and didn’t know what to do and what not to do. So I turned to my faith. I was called back to the Kingdom and had a calling for a new role as a leader in the divine feminine, which I believe will bring so much healing. It will heal us from the feminist movement and the patriarchy that have all lead to suffering in women. 

I look forward to sharing more about a few of my new journies. Thank you for being here with me 🥰❤️‍🔥

Enjoying some beautiful geological wonders of the world in the Fire Valley in the desert of Nevada.

Here are some interesting facts about this incredible wonder of the world and the hiking for the nature enthusiasts like me:

Hikers often compare trekking in Nevada’s Valley of Fire State Park to the feeling of stepping foot on Planet Mars. The orange and rust-red colored Aztec sandstone outcrops transport you to what feels like a different planet. And from space — when the sun sets — NASA scientists report that the sandstone appears to be on fire.

With more than 40,000 acres to explore in the park, you can hike through narrow slot canyons, awe at vibrantly colored paths, feel the texture of sandstone and discover unique rock formations — all shaped millions of years ago during the Jurassic Period when dinosaurs still roamed the Earth. Park rangers refer to the area as “An Island of Red Rock in the Desert.”

Be sure to get your shots at The Fire Wave
The White Dunes
Mouse Tank Road 

The weather is extremely hot and dusty so pack lots of water and plan for a half day.

888 💎 Save this post for when you need to remember who TF you are!

Self acceptance….
It’s accepting yourself exactly as you are right now all the good, the bad and the ugly. 

It’s not hiding the ugly parts and the shameful past.
It’s simply owning your truth. 
I didn’t have to share publicly about my past, I chose to because I didn’t want those secrets in the dark holding power over me. 

I accept me and all my light and darkness.
I accept my good and bad days.
I accept myself when I’m my ideal weight and when I’m 100 pounds overweight.

I accept and share my wins. 
I also accept and share my losses.

I accept myself when I’m energetic and joyful and also when I have depressive episodes where getting out of bed is a struggle. 

I accept myself when I’m a nominee for Mom of the year and also when I have bad mom days. 

I have found that the deeper I become rooted in my own self love and self acceptance, the more immune I become to criticism. I literally do not care what anybody thinks of me and how I live my life. I have never felt so free.

Confidence comes when you accept and love yourself fully and arent afraid to show up as YOU. Only then we experience that deep need for belonging, when you accept yourself, you don’t need acceptance from anybody else. 
How can you attract what’s meant for you and walk in your purpose when you aren’t even showing up as the real internal you?!

Ive noticed that people with false confidence shatter with the slightest criticism. Confident people are immune to criticism. They know what they are good at, and what they are not good at already. They are open to constructive feedback. They usually have done a lot of internal work so insults only lead them to wondering if you’re actually ok or if you need help. 😆

Im not trying to be perfect. I just want to progress and learn in my own lane, on my own authentic journey with minimal input from anybody else.

Self acceptance frees you from the need to ever compare yourself to anybody else. You know you have your own unique special journey and you’re happy for others.

After all, the same light you see shining in others can be seen shining in you too 🫶🏻

Ingredients
▢ 3 cups cooked quinoa 
▢ 1 teaspoon oil
▢ 1 1/4 lb large peeled and deveined shrimp, chopped into chunks
▢ 1-1/2 cups fresh pineapple, diced (from 2 fresh)
▢ 5 large scallions, chopped
▢ 3 cloves garlic, minced
▢ 1 fresh chili pepper or jalepeno, chopped
▢ 1 tablespoon soy sauce, or more to taste
▢ 1 teaspoon fish sauce & sesame oil 
A variety of mixed veggies of choice. I use peppers, bok choy, corn, carrots, green beans. Dice. 

Instructions
Cook quinoa according to package directions and set aside to cool.
If making pineapple bowls, cut each pineapple in half and hollow out both halves to make 4 bowls.
Cut a piece off the bottom of the pineapple halves to create a flat base.
Cut the pineapple into small pieces and set aside.
Heat a nonstick wok on high heat; when hot add oil garlic and onions.
Add shrimp and cook a few minutes until just opaque, 3 to 5 minutes; 
Add veggies and sauté until soft then add quinoa. 
Add soy sauce and fish sauce, stir to mix all the ingredients and cook another 3 minutes. 
Divide and transfer into the hollowed out pineapples and garnish with scallions

Ingredients
 
Servings: 6 servings
3/4 lb pasta
1 lb large raw shrimp, peeled and deveined (21-25 ct)
1 Tbsp olive oil
1/2 onion, (medium), finely chopped 
1/2 block cream cheese 
2 Tbsp unsalted butter
1 garlic clove, minced
1/3 cup white wine, I used Chardonnay
2 cups chopped broccoli 
2 cups cream
1/3 cup shredded parmesan cheese
1/2 tsp Sea salt, or to taste
1/4 tsp black pepper, or to taste
1/4 tsp paprika, or to taste
1 Tbsp Parsley, finely chopped, to garnish

Instructions

Add 3/4 lb pasta to a pot of boiling water with 1 Tbsp salt and cook according to package instructions until al-dente. Drain without rinsing and set aside.
While pasta is cooking, prepare the shrimp and sauce. Season shrimp with 1/2 tsp salt, 1/4 tsp black pepper and 1/4 tsp paprika. Place a large, non-stick pan over medium/high heat and add 1 Tbsp oil. Once oil is hot, add shrimp in a single layer and cook 2 min per side or just until cooked through and no longer translucent. Remove to a separate dish to prevent overcooking.

In the same hot pan, add 2 Tbsp butter with finely chopped onion and sauté until soft and golden (3-5 mins), stirring often. Add minced garlic and sauté another minute until fragrant. Stir in 1/3 cup white wine and boil down until there is only 25% of the liquid left.
Stir in 2 cups cream, bring to a light boil then simmer 2 min. Add broccoli.
Sprinkle sauce with 1/3 cup parmesan cheese and stir just until creamy and smooth. Let it come just to a simmer without boiling then turn off the heat and season sauce with more salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Stir in the drained pasta and cooked shrimp, tossing until noodles are well coated in sauce. Serve in warm pasta bowls with a generous sprinkle of finely chopped parsley, more parmesan cheese and some freshly cracked black pepper

As a business mentor for city of Kitchener I have talked to a lot of inspiring and new entrepreneurs and these are the top 3 ways I see people self sabotage their dreams and get in their own way.
I’m also going to include how to get out of your head and get out of your own way.

1. Fear. Majority of people I talk to stay focused on what will go wrong instead of staying focused on what can go right and what they want. 

2. Not clearly defining what they want, goals and objectives. I ask people what they want and they say more…more what?! They usually don’t even know. If you don’t know what you want how the heck will anybody else?! 🤔 your spouse, business partner, your employees, clients etc. Clearly define what you want with S.M.A.R.T goals strategy.

3. Allowing others opinions to block them. The majority of your well intentioned friends and families have zero experience in what you’re trying to achieve and they see life through own lens and self sabotaging beliefs. You can’t listen to them. You need to stay focused on your vision and connect with mentors who can see the big picture and help you get out of your way from an objective yet experienced point of view.

If you need help brainstorming and planning you can book a 30 minute call for $30. Link in my bio.

The Starter Company Plus (SCP) Program is for business owners operating less than 5 years (market ready and ready to sell), ready to expand (hiring employees, contractors, or getting a location), or buying a business in Waterloo Region.
This is a provincial program so you can find a similar program in your region that will provide you free support and up to $5000 grant to start or grow your start up company.
The grants are for people who complete the program and a grant committee review made up of local business professionals and private sector stakeholders.

Applications reopen in 2024 but you can book free consultations with the city of Kitchener or book and pay privately with the individual city mentors.

Have an idea or a goal?
Here’s how to formulate it into a plan:

1. Play some good music for inspo. Currently I have Losing Control by @vybzkartel on repeat 
2. Brainstorm on a sketch pad with pen and paper
3. Research & learn skills you made need or hire key staff
4. Make the goals SMART, specific, measurable, attainable, relatable and timely
5. create a strategy involving key contacts, costs, budget, how you will track progress and what it’s gonna take to get there
6. Create a timeline
7. Track progress & revisit often to adjust plan as needed
8. Put in on a highly visible vision board
9. Use excel and word templates to keep it on a computer as well
10. Learn from mistakes and always keep pushing forward! Setbacks failures and losses are inevitable. Keep going ❤️

WHAT YOU NEED TO MAKE A TRUE NEWF POUTINE!!!

Its very simple really and also very quick to make using only a few simple ingredients.

French fries
cheese curds
Poutine gravy or gravy mix
Newfoundland Stuffing or boxed stuffing
Optional: leftover Turkey 

  WHAT YOU NEED TO MAKE NEWFOUNDLAND DRESSING

2 cups (60g) fresh white coarse bread crumbs
1 - 2 TBS summer savory ( this is an herb)
1 small onion, peeled and finely chopped
6 TBS butter
1/4 cup water or chicken bouillon (60ml), only if dressing seems dry
salt and black pepper to taste 

GRAVY:
Melt 1/4 cup butter and whisk in 3/4 cup flour
Add two cups turkey drippings or broth and whisk until desired consistency over medium heat. Add a splash of gravy browning for Color.

Fry sliced potatoes covered in canola oil until golden brown and dab in a paper towel to get off excess grease. Or feel free to use alternative premade fries. From scratch is always best and most rewarding. 

ASSEMBLE:
Fries, dressing, turkey, cheese and hot gravy on top.

Enjoy ☺️ 🤤
